tweet_text: Today we celebrate Shirley Chisholm,  In 1968 she became the first black woman elected to the United States Congress. Congress Women Shirley Chisholm represented New York's 12th congressional district, Congress Women Shirley Chisholm serviced seven terms from 1969 to 1983.

name: Rep. Danny K. Davis
tweet_text: In 1972  she became the first black candidate for a major-party nomination to run for President of the United States, and also the first woman to run for the Democratic Party. She was Born in Brooklyn, New York, on November 30, 1924

tweet_text: Chisholm was the oldest of four daughters to immigrant parents from Barbados. Her motto and title of her autobiography ‚ÄúUnbought and Unbossed‚Äù illustrates advocating  for women and minorities during her seven terms in the U.S. House of Representatives.
